page.title: 03Housing & Jobs in w. Strood
page.content: This part of Strood, bordered to the north by the A2 and to the south-west by the M2, is strictly residential. The housing estates have gradually been added, many in the last thirty years, to cater for the growing population of the Medway Towns. The housing varies in quality, from some depressed areas to some relatively expensive estates. This part of Strood is less densely populated than those to the east, towards the centre of Rochester. Almost all houses in the area have small gardens. There is very little employment within this area. The vast majority drive or use bus services into the Medway Towns to work.
